[size=8pt][u]This is for my Delta cleaned souce. [/u] [/size] 

[size=10pt]This will all be done in client.java[/size]

Find you'r Login message . In my case it'll be
<blockquote>sM("Welcome to RuneWorld");</blockquote>

Above that Add this

<blockquote>talk1("#TEXT#"0);</blockquote>

Soo compile And test . you should have 1 line of text in a dialogue when you log in. 

I will show you how to add more lines of text

2 lines of text
<blockquote>talk2("Welcome to RuneWorld","Follow the rules and read the help guide",0);</blockquote>

3 lines of text
<blockquote>talk3("Welcome to RuneWorld","Follow the rules and read the help guide","LALALALALALA",0);</blockquote>

4 lines of text
<blockquote>talk4("Welcome to RuneWorld","Follow the rules and read the help guide","LALALALALALA","LALALALALALALA",0);</blockquote>


[b][size=10pt]For the 3 and 4 lined text to work you may need theese method's Other wise you will get errors[/size][/b]

<blockquote>public void talk3(String text, String text2, String text3, int npc) {
		sendFrame200(4901, 591);
		sendFrame126(GetNpcName(npc), 4902);
		sendFrame126("", 4903);
		sendFrame126(text, 4904);
		sendFrame126(text2, 4905);
		sendFrame126(text3, 4906);
		sendFrame75(npc, 4901);
		sendFrame164(4900);
	}
	public void talk4(String text, String text2, String text3,  String text4, int npc) {
		sendFrame200(4901, 591);
		sendFrame126(GetNpcName(npc), 4902);
		sendFrame126(text, 4903);
		sendFrame126(text2, 4904);
		sendFrame126(text3, 4905);
		sendFrame126(text4, 4906);
		sendFrame75(npc, 4901);
		sendFrame164(4900);
	}</blockquote>

Of course you can figure where the text goes.
The " 0 " at the very end of each code is the npc ID you want it to show.  In my case Mines "Hans"

